results.name: Decimal expansion of Sum_{n>=2} (-1)^n/(n*phi(n)), where phi(n) is the Euler totient function A000010.
comment: The formula section of A000010 provides the following conjecture: Limit Sum_{i>=2} (-1)^i/(i*phi(i)) exists and is approximately 0.558. - Orges Leka (oleka(AT)students.uni-mainz.de), Dec 23 2004
A more accurate value of the conjectured limit is provided.
results.author: _Hugo Pfoertner_, May 31 2020
